The paper deals with coding for discrete channels and signal constellations, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of poset-decoders for unequal error protection is a technique that falls under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the concept of semantic value of information, which is related to the field of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The use of loss functions to evaluate coding schemes is a topic that falls under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper also presents some results related to signal constellations in Euclidean space, which is a topic covered in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
